00:43.919 --> 00:45.712
Hey, take it easy will ya!

00:45.921 --> 00:47.380
Hey, who's the big birthday girl, huh?

00:47.589 --> 00:49.465
- Me!
- Oh boy, hey how old are you?

00:49.675 --> 00:50.758
I'm this!

00:50.968 --> 00:52.927
Well call me when you're this, okay.

00:53.137 --> 00:54.303
All right here we go now.

00:54.513 --> 00:56.180
You got it straight, okay?
Hold it there.

00:56.390 --> 00:59.100
Hey, beautiful, beautiful! Okay!

01:08.652 --> 01:11.487
Hey, what happened here?
What's the matter, huh?

01:11.697 --> 01:14.282
Johnny hit me. He don't like me anymore.

01:14.491 --> 01:17.577
Oh, I know what you're
goin' through, ya know.

01:17.786 --> 01:20.079
You gave him the best three
months of your life, huh?

01:20.289 --> 01:22.457
Then he left you for a pail and shovel.

01:23.083 --> 01:25.418
What do you see in him, anyway?
What are you in love with?

01:25.627 --> 01:30.673
He's not in your class. He's afraid
of the dark. He wets his pants.

01:31.133 --> 01:34.927
When he eats, he gets food all
over his face. He's a mama's boy.

01:35.137 --> 01:36.929
What are you, in nursery school now?

01:37.139 --> 01:39.348
I guarantee you, by the time
you get to kindergarten,

01:39.558 --> 01:41.934
you'll forget all about him, okay?

01:42.144 --> 01:45.730
Hey, look who's here!
Show time! Bobby Bunny, huh?

01:48.609 --> 01:51.986
Here we go, kids, let's go here.
Bobby Bunny's here...

01:52.196 --> 01:55.031
- What's that?
- Oh, nothing, nothing.

01:55.574 --> 01:58.969
Bobby Bunny just dropped
a few carrots, that's all.

05:18.318 --> 05:19.944
Well, let's go over today's schedule.

05:20.153 --> 05:23.197
It is exactly 6:33.

05:23.407 --> 05:26.242
It is exactly 6:34.

05:26.785 --> 05:28.327
At 7:00, we're meeting with the

05:28.537 --> 05:31.205
head of the furniture department
regarding inventory.

05:31.415 --> 05:34.375
Postpone the meeting.
Double-check the inventory,

05:34.584 --> 05:36.585
and fire the cleaning staff.

05:36.795 --> 05:39.088
7:20, you will crush the hopes
of the loading dock workers

05:39.298 --> 05:41.173
regarding better working conditions.

05:41.383 --> 05:43.175
Cancel the meeting,
and send out a memorandum

05:43.385 --> 05:45.678
that the working conditions
at the loading dock

05:45.887 --> 05:48.764
will remain as they have for
the past 35 years.

05:48.974 --> 05:50.099
Mm-hmm.

05:50.309 --> 05:52.184
At 7:30, we'll be meeting
with the accountants

05:52.394 --> 05:55.104
regarding donations and
charitable contributions.

05:55.314 --> 05:58.399
Cancel that meeting,
and cancel my check to Boy's Town.

05:59.443 --> 06:01.235
What time is Scrappleton coming?

06:01.445 --> 06:05.114
Uh, 7:50, with the legal
papers you requested.

06:05.949 --> 06:09.243
As soon as you finish with Scrappleton,
we leave for New Dorp, Staten Island

06:09.453 --> 06:11.996
to attend your granddaughter
Allison's wedding.

06:12.205 --> 06:15.249
Well, I hope she's made a better choice

06:15.459 --> 06:17.293
than her mother did!

06:17.961 --> 06:20.129
Jesus! Rose!

06:21.548 --> 06:23.716
How did you talk me into this?

06:25.510 --> 06:27.845
You should use Allison.
She's the one who has to wear it.

06:28.055 --> 06:31.349
It's unlucky for the bride to wear
her gown before the wedding day.

06:31.558 --> 06:33.434
How unlucky can she get,
look who she's marrying.

06:33.643 --> 06:35.353
Come on dear,
you shouldn't talk like that.

06:35.562 --> 06:37.855
Julio's a good boy.
Come on, Rose, will ya?

06:38.065 --> 06:40.941
See the guy for what he is.
He belongs to a gang.

06:41.151 --> 06:43.861
It's a good boy's gang.
They help people.

06:44.071 --> 06:47.907
- Ooh, take it easy, will ya?
- Oh, I'm sorry. Where'd I get you?

06:48.116 --> 06:50.534
If I show you where you got me
we'll never get outta here.

06:50.744 --> 06:52.495
All right, hold still.
I've gotta finish this.

06:52.704 --> 06:55.623
You gotta pick up the cake,
and mother will be here soon.

06:56.500 --> 06:58.376
Your mother.

06:59.169 --> 07:02.254
I gotta go to the john.
Monty! Oh, the dress!

07:02.464 --> 07:05.883
- No, you're wonderful.
- Allison, I need the phone.

07:06.093 --> 07:08.719
- I'm in here!
- Come on, get outta there!

07:09.262 --> 07:11.889
- Get off, will ya?
- I am so hung up on you.

07:12.099 --> 07:14.892
Good idea. I'll see you in church.

07:15.102 --> 07:15.851
Daddy!

07:16.061 --> 07:17.895
Don't worry, you won't
lose him, all right.

07:18.105 --> 07:19.730
Belinda, let's go.

07:20.607 --> 07:23.401
Someday I'll be out of your life.

07:23.610 --> 07:25.986
Yeah, right now get outta
the bathroom, all right.

07:42.003 --> 07:43.963
The best thing about having daughters.

07:59.563 --> 08:01.647
Nicky boy, it's Monty.

08:03.650 --> 08:05.109
Close the door.

08:07.612 --> 08:08.654
Yeah?

08:08.864 --> 08:10.865
Nicky, Rose's mother,
she's on her way over.

08:12.075 --> 08:13.868
So? What do you want from me?

08:14.077 --> 08:16.203
I need the truck.
I gotta pick up the wedding cake.

08:16.413 --> 08:17.997
What am I supposed to be, Allied Vans?

08:18.206 --> 08:19.999
You really know how to push
a friendship, you know?

08:20.208 --> 08:22.084
When's the last time
you did something for me?

08:22.294 --> 08:23.961
Hey Monty you got a
short memory, you know?

08:24.171 --> 08:25.504
Who drove all the way
down to Atlantic City

08:25.714 --> 08:27.339
to bail you out when you owed $400?

08:27.591 --> 08:29.467
At Belmont, you had
four losers in a row.

08:29.676 --> 08:30.843
Who gave you the winner in the fifth?

08:31.052 --> 08:32.970
The cake's for your godchild,
you ungrateful bastard you!

08:33.179 --> 08:36.056
All right, all right.
Give me a chance. I'm comin'.

08:47.110 --> 08:50.988
- Where's my stuff?
- By the front door. What's the rush?

08:51.198 --> 08:53.282
I gotta go to work.
I got a wedding to pay for.

08:53.492 --> 08:55.034
Don't forget the cake.

08:55.243 --> 08:58.824
How many years you know me?
Did I ever forget anything?

08:59.247 --> 09:01.624
Nicky, just in time. Beautiful!

09:01.833 --> 09:05.419
I don't wanna see her fucking... mother!

09:08.256 --> 09:11.717
- Was it Nicky?
- No, no. It's not Nicky. No.

09:13.261 --> 09:15.846
- Oh, it's mother!
- Leave him, dear.

09:16.056 --> 09:18.140
Just simply walk out on him.

09:18.350 --> 09:21.727
His entire body is bloodshot.
He'll never change.

09:22.270 --> 09:24.146
Nice to see you too.

09:24.356 --> 09:26.607
It's gonna be so much
fun having everyone here.

09:26.816 --> 09:28.692
Yeah, a lot of fun, a lot of fun.

09:28.902 --> 09:30.861
Well, if it isn't my favorite relative.

09:31.071 --> 09:33.072
Oh, don't start that bullshit, all right.

09:33.281 --> 09:35.866
Monty, please bring
mother's luggage upstairs.

09:36.910 --> 09:40.746
- Well what's Clive, a footstool?
- No, no, Monty, let me get this.

09:43.291 --> 09:47.169
- How can you stand him?
- You've gotta get to know him.

09:47.379 --> 09:49.630
The wedding is gonna be wonderful.

09:50.173 --> 09:51.966
We never get to see you.

09:52.175 --> 09:54.593
The store takes up all my time.

09:56.805 --> 09:58.806
Mother, why do you push
yourself so hard?

09:59.015 --> 10:00.558
The money doesn't matter.

10:00.767 --> 10:04.687
When your father was alive,
he ran Monahan's like a tyrant.

10:04.896 --> 10:06.689
He paid the help next to nothing.

10:06.898 --> 10:09.733
- He drove them like sled dogs.
- Wonderful man.

10:09.943 --> 10:14.113
Wonderful! Now that he's gone,
I carry on his work.

10:14.322 --> 10:15.739
Rose,

10:15.949 --> 10:20.744
I don't know how you can
live with that man.

10:20.954 --> 10:23.247
We're happy just the way we are.

10:23.456 --> 10:27.293
Happy? Yeah, we were
until a few minutes ago.

10:27.836 --> 10:30.212
And we don't want a dime from you.
You understand?

10:30.422 --> 10:31.755
No offense.

10:33.925 --> 10:35.342
No offense?

10:35.552 --> 10:37.136
No offense?

10:37.345 --> 10:39.722
You are an offense!

10:39.931 --> 10:42.725
Why, you can barely walk erect.

10:43.184 --> 10:46.353
You pollute the air with your smoking.

10:46.563 --> 10:48.731
You reek of liquor and
God knows what else.

10:48.940 --> 10:50.274
You're an ecological menace!

10:50.483 --> 10:52.693
Yeah, well you were the
inspiration for twin beds.

10:52.902 --> 10:54.486
And I'll tell you something else...

10:54.696 --> 10:56.196
Monty, don't start with mother.

10:56.406 --> 10:58.198
I'm not startin' nothin'.
It never ended.

10:58.408 --> 11:01.785
And to think of who you could
have married. Pat Flannigan.

11:01.995 --> 11:02.828
Do me a favor, will ya,

11:03.038 --> 11:05.289
don't start throwing up the
guys she could've married.

11:05.498 --> 11:06.999
He started out as a bricklayer.

11:07.208 --> 11:09.668
Now he owns his own
construction company.

11:09.878 --> 11:12.254
And what about Tom O'Rourke?
He started as a busboy.

11:12.464 --> 11:14.673
Today he has his own restaurant.

11:14.883 --> 11:18.761
Oh, yeah, I started out as a baby.
Today I'm a baby photographer.

11:18.970 --> 11:20.137
I'll see you later.

11:20.347 --> 11:23.307
And I'm sure you're gonna
talk about me when I'm gone.

11:35.028 --> 11:37.988
Where do you live, in Vermont?
What took you so long?

11:49.542 --> 11:51.543
Why do you let her mother get to you?

11:51.753 --> 11:53.796
Forget about her, will ya?

11:54.756 --> 11:57.049
She never wanted Rose
to marry me. Never.

12:00.178 --> 12:03.555
She says I drink too much,
I smoke too much, I gamble.

12:03.765 --> 12:05.641
She's right, but what am I gonna do?

12:05.850 --> 12:07.059
I can't control myself.

12:07.268 --> 12:10.354
I got no, uh, what's the word
I'm looking for, I got no...

12:10.563 --> 12:11.480
Class.

12:11.690 --> 12:14.108
Nah, we know I got class, no.

12:14.317 --> 12:15.901
It's a certain word I'm looking' for.

12:16.111 --> 12:18.529
What's the word for someone
who can't say "no"?

12:18.738 --> 12:21.073
- Sonya.
- Not Sonya. No, not Sonya.

12:21.324 --> 12:23.158
No, I got no...

12:24.160 --> 12:25.953
Willpower! That's the word
I'm lookin' for.

12:26.162 --> 12:28.122
Willpower, I got no willpower.
That's what it is.

12:28.331 --> 12:29.540
Yeah, willpower.

12:29.749 --> 12:32.084
Make a left on Elm. I got a quick shoot.

12:32.293 --> 12:34.086
What shoot? You didn't say
anything about a shoot.

12:34.295 --> 12:36.588
Leave me alone. I got enough
problems. Just take a left on Elm.

12:36.798 --> 12:39.091
I got a quick shoot. I'll be quick.
You can help me, all right.

12:39.300 --> 12:40.634
Oh, I can help you. Well, thanks.

12:40.844 --> 12:43.220
You really think I got no class?

12:43.430 --> 12:45.514
No, I don't think you got no class.

12:45.724 --> 12:49.518
I'm gonna be sad. Mmmmm.
Very good, okay!

12:49.728 --> 12:52.224
Now, I'm gonna be a monster.
Watch this, okay.

12:53.523 --> 12:55.399
Now the big one. Okay, the big one.

12:55.608 --> 12:57.151
Can you be happy?

12:57.360 --> 13:00.154
That's a good one! Okay, be happy.

13:00.363 --> 13:02.656
Okay, here we are. Smile pretty.

13:02.866 --> 13:04.950
Beautiful! There we go, we got it.

13:12.584 --> 13:14.126
The other door. The other door!

13:14.335 --> 13:16.128
- I got it, I got it.
- The other door!

13:27.390 --> 13:31.101
- Get outta here.
- Oooh! Oh!

13:36.649 --> 13:38.233
The cake, the cake!

13:43.656 --> 13:46.867
- Watch out for the top.
- I'm watching, I'm watching.

13:48.787 --> 13:50.370
It's not gonna slide
around in there, is it?

13:50.622 --> 13:52.456
No, I got it wedged against a toilet.

13:59.881 --> 14:02.549
This is just great.
My favorite system a lock.

14:02.759 --> 14:04.676
And I got Monty in the truck
with a wedding cake.

14:04.886 --> 14:06.762
I gotta pick up my mother,
take her to the beauty parlor.

14:07.013 --> 14:10.599
- What's the tip?
- Big Boy in the fifth.

14:11.434 --> 14:13.685
Forget it! The fifth goes off at 3:00.

14:13.895 --> 14:17.689
- We goin' to the track?
- I can't go. I got a bar to run.

14:17.899 --> 14:19.233
This here's a sure thing.

14:19.442 --> 14:22.236
- It's forty to one.
- Hey!

14:22.445 --> 14:25.614
- Wake up, we're closing up.
- I didn't finish my drink yet.

14:25.824 --> 14:29.243
You're finished now. Get outta here.
Here's your dollar.

14:33.456 --> 14:36.625
Come on, come on will ya.
We've got five minutes to post.

14:43.216 --> 14:45.092
Hey! Get the hell out of there!

14:45.301 --> 14:48.011
Slow down, will ya, slow down.
They're kids.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.682
Nicky, take care of it.

14:58.231 --> 15:00.090
What're you doing?

15:04.279 --> 15:06.822
Sixty seconds to post time.

15:09.117 --> 15:10.784
Are you gonna place a bet or what?

15:10.994 --> 15:15.414
Oh, yes, yes. I'd like the
number seven horse please.

15:15.623 --> 15:17.875
Thirty seconds to post time.

15:18.084 --> 15:23.380
I'd like to put two dollars to win,
and two dollars to place

15:23.590 --> 15:27.384
- and two dollars to show.
- Okay, buddy, good luck.

15:27.594 --> 15:32.389
The next time you bet,
remember, instead of saying

15:32.599 --> 15:34.516
two dollars to win,
two dollars to place,

15:34.726 --> 15:37.895
two dollars to show, just say,
"two across the board."

15:38.104 --> 15:41.106
- Gee, you mean instead of saying...
- What are you buyin', a house?

15:41.316 --> 15:42.399
Two dollars to place...

15:42.609 --> 15:44.902
Let's go while we're young.

15:45.111 --> 15:46.904
We're gonna get shut out!

15:47.113 --> 15:49.364
Yes, I have a friend
that wants to bet the

15:49.574 --> 15:50.991
number seven horse.

15:52.660 --> 15:55.078
Number six horse. Six horse.

15:55.288 --> 15:57.080
No more bets.

15:59.250 --> 16:01.335
And they're off!

16:04.505 --> 16:09.009
Nicky, come on. We're goin' to the rail.

16:10.053 --> 16:12.429
Big Boy making up lots
of ground on the outside,

16:12.639 --> 16:14.723
moving to the fourth spot.

16:14.933 --> 16:17.935
Here comes Big Boy with a rush
on the extreme outside.

16:18.978 --> 16:20.312
How's he doin'? How's he doin'?

16:20.521 --> 16:23.231
- Gettin' farther ahead all the time.
- Gimme those things.

16:25.443 --> 16:27.235
Five lengths ahead!

16:27.445 --> 16:29.363
Fifty bucks at forty to one!

16:29.572 --> 16:32.616
That's two grand apiece!
Two grand apiece!

16:35.328 --> 16:38.747
You dragged me out here,
you bastards, I love ya, I love ya!

16:48.424 --> 16:50.876
That's two grand apiece! Two G's!

16:54.597 --> 16:56.807
I'm goin' to Hawaii!
I'm goin' to Hawaii!

16:57.016 --> 16:59.935
- He's fallin' back.
- I'm not goin' to Hawaii!

17:02.981 --> 17:04.647
He's too far ahead to lose.

17:13.116 --> 17:15.367
Look at him!
He thinks he's water skiing!

17:17.744 --> 17:20.204
- We were in. What happened?
- Yeah, there's our winner.

17:20.748 --> 17:23.625
I closed my bar! Get outta here!

17:23.835 --> 17:26.627
I'll kill you.

17:26.838 --> 17:29.131
I'll kill you, Bosco!

17:29.340 --> 17:32.134
I'll kill him. I'll kill you!

17:32.343 --> 17:35.721
There was supposed to be a fix. Crooks!

17:36.014 --> 17:39.099
I was gonna buy a new neon sign.

17:43.646 --> 17:45.522
Yeah, that's it. Step on his face!

17:45.732 --> 17:47.882
That son of a bitch!

17:56.534 --> 17:59.494
Go get him, Nicky!

17:59.704 --> 18:02.581
My bridesmaids' dresses are lime green.

18:02.790 --> 18:06.084
And my maid of honor
is wearing lime green.

18:06.377 --> 18:08.754
The maid of honor's dress should
always be in contrast

18:08.963 --> 18:09.796
to the bridesmaids.

18:10.006 --> 18:14.176
This is, um, delicious!
What do you call it?

18:14.385 --> 18:15.302
Chicken!

18:15.511 --> 18:17.929
I know it's chicken, dear,
but what kind?

18:18.139 --> 18:19.306
There's Kiev, there's Florentine...

18:19.515 --> 18:21.808
Shake & bake!

18:22.018 --> 18:23.810
Mother, I'm glad you could come.

18:24.020 --> 18:26.813
I've always been sorry
you missed my wedding.

18:27.023 --> 18:28.607
You know I couldn't go to your wedding.

18:28.816 --> 18:29.816
That's cause Daddy was there.

18:30.026 --> 18:32.194
Where is your father tonight, dear?

18:32.403 --> 18:33.528
He's taking baby pictures.

18:33.738 --> 18:38.408
Ha! What kind of a baby is it
that's still up at 9 at night?

18:51.422 --> 18:52.839
Sweetheart, watch out for this guy.

18:53.049 --> 18:55.842
He'll buy you a bottle of beer,
and squeeze the "schlitz" outta ya.

18:56.052 --> 18:57.677
Who is this guy?

18:57.887 --> 19:00.347
He's my friend. Don't worry about him.

19:00.556 --> 19:04.351
Excuse me, miss. I don't mean
to interrupt while you're working.

19:04.560 --> 19:08.105
I was wondering if you could
come over to the house

19:08.314 --> 19:11.358
Sunday for dinner and meet my mother?

19:11.567 --> 19:13.860
- Do you wanna go home?
- He's kiddin' around.

19:14.070 --> 19:17.364
Excuse me, pal. You got a problem here?
This is my friend.

19:17.573 --> 19:19.908
- Who are you?
- Who am I?

19:20.118 --> 19:21.827
I'm the guy that put
the bathrooms in this joint.

19:22.036 --> 19:22.619
That's who I am.

19:22.829 --> 19:25.663
Now I know why the place
stinks, okay, pal?

19:27.708 --> 19:30.168
Break it up, will ya? What's the matter?

19:32.713 --> 19:34.673
Take it easy, will ya?

19:36.509 --> 19:38.969
- Ma?
- Hmm?

19:39.512 --> 19:41.388
Am I pretty?

19:41.597 --> 19:43.974
Oh, you're beautiful, sweetheart.

19:44.517 --> 19:46.393
Julio's a very lucky boy.

19:47.603 --> 19:49.896
I wanna make him happy.

19:50.106 --> 19:51.898
But there's so much I don't know.

19:52.108 --> 19:55.402
- Like what?
- Like about, you know.

19:55.611 --> 19:58.488
- I know what?
- You know!

20:00.032 --> 20:01.950
Oh, that.

20:02.160 --> 20:04.452
Didn't your father tell you
everything you need to know?

20:04.662 --> 20:07.956
He keeps starting,
but he never finishes.

20:08.166 --> 20:10.625
What do you wanna know?

20:11.919 --> 20:15.005
Foreplay. Have you
ever heard of foreplay?

20:15.256 --> 20:17.924
No, not with your father.

20:18.134 --> 20:20.927
It's nice we can have
these little talks.

20:21.137 --> 20:22.679
Let's go help Belinda pour the coffee.

20:22.889 --> 20:23.430
Wait, Mom.

20:23.639 --> 20:25.515
How did you know that
you really loved Daddy?

20:26.058 --> 20:29.519
We were at Coney Island
on the ferris wheel.

20:30.062 --> 20:31.938
We got caught at the top.

20:32.148 --> 20:34.024
Later on, I found out

20:34.567 --> 20:37.944
he paid the man a dollar
to stop the ride.

20:38.154 --> 20:40.447
Your father said things to me

20:40.656 --> 20:44.534
that were so sweet, so romantic.

20:45.077 --> 20:49.539
I said to myself,
"Here's a sensitive man."

20:49.832 --> 20:52.209
Just once, a fuckin' four!

20:52.418 --> 20:55.212
Four! Got a four!

20:55.421 --> 20:57.214
Gimme the dice, I'm hot. Gimme the dice.

20:57.423 --> 21:00.217
Hold it, hold it! You won, right?

21:00.426 --> 21:02.719
We're ahead.
We can leave winners right now.

21:02.929 --> 21:04.221
Okay, so we go. Let's go.

21:04.430 --> 21:07.224
Double or nothin'. Come on, here we go.

21:07.433 --> 21:10.310
Oh, Monty!

21:30.915 --> 21:32.791
You did it again, huh?

21:34.335 --> 21:36.836
We were winners.
We could've walked away.

21:37.964 --> 21:40.674
That's how I am.
Once I get goin', I can't stop.

21:50.393 --> 21:54.354
Come on. Forget about it.
It's history. Let's go.

21:59.902 --> 22:03.280
Good stuff. It oughta be.
I got it off a cop.

22:03.489 --> 22:07.450
- I'm starvin'.
- Let's go to Lucky's. He's open late.

22:21.882 --> 22:23.258
He's closed.

22:23.467 --> 22:26.386
Come on, Pop's inside. He'll let us in.

22:39.942 --> 22:41.818
Pop's last dish.

22:42.028 --> 22:43.778
We're drivin' a half hour.

22:43.988 --> 22:46.197
The closest we came to food,
we almost hit a deer.

22:46.407 --> 22:47.991
Hey, there's a place.

23:00.421 --> 23:03.048
I'm so hungry, I could eat the waitress.

23:18.481 --> 23:21.441
No, no! No! It's wrong.
Nicky, it's wrong.

23:21.650 --> 23:24.361
- I just wanna see what...
- It's wrong!

23:25.905 --> 23:28.865
It's wedding cake flavor.
I love wedding cake.

23:29.116 --> 23:30.784
Why don't you get married?

23:33.996 --> 23:35.997
Let me just lick the bride.

23:37.083 --> 23:38.875
That's my daughter!

23:39.085 --> 23:42.921
It's a little plastic thing.
It's not your daughter.

23:46.008 --> 23:48.885
Only one little flower each.

23:49.095 --> 23:51.888
There's a lot of little flowers.
Nobody will know the difference.

23:52.098 --> 23:54.391
Forget about it. Let's get outta here.

23:54.600 --> 23:56.976
And don't drive fast. You're drunk.

23:57.520 --> 23:59.979
Don't worry about it.
I drive better when I'm drunk.

24:05.027 --> 24:07.404
You got a weird sense of humor.
You know that?

24:07.613 --> 24:09.781
You laugh at everything.
Weather reports, car chase.

24:09.990 --> 24:11.449
You laugh at everything.

24:11.659 --> 24:13.952
Keep it straight, will ya?
You're swerving all over the place.

24:14.161 --> 24:16.830
I'm goin' straight.
I'm on the yellow line, I told ya.

24:17.039 --> 24:19.165
Move over to one side.
The other side! What are ya doin?

24:19.375 --> 24:21.543
You're on the other side! Get over here!

24:21.752 --> 24:23.670
- Keep to the right!
- Get your hands off the wheel!

24:23.879 --> 24:25.338
Nicky look out!

24:30.177 --> 24:32.912
My head! I hit my head!

24:34.265 --> 24:36.141
What's so funny?
Everything's funny to you.

24:36.350 --> 24:37.058
You laugh and laugh.

24:37.268 --> 24:39.561
Watch the road, will ya?
Will you watch the road?

24:39.770 --> 24:44.607
