You look beautiful.

34:36.658 --> 34:39.659
I always dreamed about my wedding day.

34:41.288 --> 34:43.621
I guess I never thought about the night.

35:07.189 --> 35:09.023
Be gentle with me.

35:20.702 --> 35:22.620
Julio!

35:22.829 --> 35:25.122
This is foreplay.

35:25.332 --> 35:29.585
- I have a headache.
- I don't wanna touch your head.

35:29.795 --> 35:32.588
Please, Julio, I've never
been with a man before.

35:32.798 --> 35:34.590
Neither have I!

35:34.800 --> 35:36.258
Julio!

35:41.223 --> 35:44.475
- What's wrong with you?
- I don't know what to do.

35:45.727 --> 35:49.105
- I brought a book.
- A book?

35:55.237 --> 35:57.113
"El Joyo de Sexo."

35:57.322 --> 36:00.157
- It's in Spanish.
- I'm gonna translate it for you.

36:00.367 --> 36:03.702
It has a very happy ending.
You're gonna love it.

36:13.213 --> 36:15.172
Allison?

36:15.757 --> 36:18.092
What do you want from me, Julio?

36:18.844 --> 36:21.428
I never seen anything like that.

36:22.848 --> 36:25.141
Try to understand.

36:25.350 --> 36:28.144
I keep hearing my father say, "Don't."

36:28.353 --> 36:31.188
He meant before you were married.

36:34.776 --> 36:38.737
I'm not so sure.
You don't know my father.

36:42.284 --> 36:44.243
Allison,

36:46.288 --> 36:47.997
listen to me.

36:50.750 --> 36:54.128
My cousin once knew a guy,

36:55.380 --> 36:59.175
and the guy went out with a virgin

36:59.384 --> 37:01.385
for six months.

37:02.888 --> 37:07.683
And on their wedding night,
when they got married,

37:07.893 --> 37:11.270
and they wanted to consummate
the marriage,

37:12.814 --> 37:15.024
the woman wouldn't let him.

37:17.819 --> 37:20.696
And in the morning,

37:20.906 --> 37:23.240
they found the guy dead

37:24.826 --> 37:27.786
in the bed next to her.

37:30.332 --> 37:33.250
- Oh.
- Allison?

37:35.420 --> 37:37.630
I don't wanna die.

37:41.843 --> 37:45.221
- You're my wife.
- Yeah.

37:45.430 --> 37:48.807
- I love you.
- Yeah.

37:49.351 --> 37:51.268
We're all alone.

37:52.938 --> 37:55.231
And your father,

37:55.440 --> 37:58.016
he is a million miles away.

38:04.866 --> 38:06.784
Hello?

38:06.993 --> 38:12.248
Julio, I just wanna say
good night to my little baby.

38:12.457 --> 38:14.291
My father!

38:18.380 --> 38:22.258
You hung up on my father?
I wouldn't hang up on your father.

38:22.467 --> 38:24.677
You wouldn't understand my father.

38:24.886 --> 38:28.264
Yeah, well, I'm not so sure
I understand you either.

38:28.473 --> 38:32.351
Well then why don't you go spend your
wedding night with your father then?

38:35.397 --> 38:37.856
Okay, I will!

38:48.285 --> 38:50.744
Monty, don't forget to fix the walk.

38:50.954 --> 38:51.996
Yeah.

39:07.929 --> 39:10.097
Watch it, watch it!
Watch where you're goin'!

39:11.933 --> 39:13.851
My air mail!

39:14.060 --> 39:15.644
Oh, my air mail!

39:28.408 --> 39:30.868
Listen to me. I want my wife back.

39:31.244 --> 39:32.870
Well, look who's here. Don Juan.

39:33.079 --> 39:36.332
- It's your fault she left me, man.
- What, am I responsible?

39:36.541 --> 39:39.293
When Eddie Fisher broke up with Debbie,
you blame me for that too, huh?

39:39.502 --> 39:40.627
She don't wanna see ya.

39:40.837 --> 39:42.880
You gotta help me, man.
You gotta help me.

39:43.089 --> 39:46.383
Give her time.
She'll come back when she's ready.

39:46.593 --> 39:48.969
You oughta give her a few drinks.

39:49.179 --> 39:51.096
That's how I got her mother ready.

39:59.689 --> 40:00.773
I'm in.

40:01.900 --> 40:03.859
- It's up to you, Paddy.
- Yeah.

40:04.861 --> 40:08.364
- What the hell is that you got on?
- This? This used to be a shirt.

40:08.573 --> 40:10.407
You know Rose.
She don't throw nothin' out.

40:10.617 --> 40:11.909
She keeps lookin' at the cuffs.

40:12.118 --> 40:14.411
Soon as they get frayed,
it becomes a short-sleeve shirt.

40:14.621 --> 40:16.914
When the collar goes,
I end up with a pajama top.

40:17.082 --> 40:19.875
Right now I got 23
short-sleeve pajama tops.

40:20.085 --> 40:23.379
You know what I found in the closet?
A hundred 1978 calendars.

40:23.588 --> 40:25.381
That's Rose!

40:25.590 --> 40:28.425
I tell ya, if 1978 ever comes back,
we're in great shape, ya know.

40:28.635 --> 40:30.928
Hey, are we gonna talk
or we gonna play cards?

40:34.265 --> 40:35.641
He'll talk.

40:39.020 --> 40:41.897
Nicky, take it easy.

40:42.107 --> 40:44.983
Take it easy, Nicky. He didn't mean it.

40:48.071 --> 40:50.197
Monty, the phone.

40:51.658 --> 40:53.492
Hello? Hello?

40:54.536 --> 40:56.995
Monty, you have to pick it up.

41:05.004 --> 41:07.881
You got the wrong number.
There's nobody home. We're asleep.

41:08.633 --> 41:11.009
Mr. Capuletti?

41:12.554 --> 41:16.014
- Are you there?
- Monty, who is it, Monty?

41:23.815 --> 41:27.609
Hello, hello! Anyone there?

41:33.825 --> 41:36.243
Who know a Scrappleton?

41:36.453 --> 41:38.787
That's mother's lawyer.

41:44.294 --> 41:47.212
Yeah. Yeah?

41:47.422 --> 41:49.882
That's awful!

41:50.842 --> 41:54.720
No, no. I'm sorry. I'll tell her.

41:54.929 --> 41:56.805
I'll tell her. I'm sorry.

41:57.849 --> 42:00.184
Monty, what happened?

42:02.353 --> 42:06.648
Rose, you better sit down for this.

42:11.362 --> 42:14.823
Is it mother?

42:15.366 --> 42:18.160
Rose, there was a plane crash.

42:19.496 --> 42:23.290
Your mother earned her wings.

42:24.334 --> 42:28.795
It's all right. It's all right, baby.

42:30.048 --> 42:31.882
"And to my nephew Clive,

42:32.091 --> 42:34.384
"son of my beloved departed brother,

42:34.594 --> 42:37.888
"whom I've undertaken to
raise as a son of my own,

42:38.097 --> 42:41.892
"in as much as he has always
led a simple, virtuous life,

42:42.101 --> 42:45.395
"and because it is my wish
that he continue to do so,

42:45.605 --> 42:50.442
"I bequeath to him an additional
income of $5,000 a year

42:50.652 --> 42:52.486
for the rest of his life."

42:52.695 --> 42:55.989
Ah there must be some mistake, Dan.

42:56.533 --> 42:59.952
- There must be some more zeroes.
- No.

43:00.161 --> 43:01.954
Um, a comma?

43:02.163 --> 43:03.956
No.

43:04.499 --> 43:06.500
"To my beloved daughter, Rose,

43:06.793 --> 43:10.671
"burdened as she is with
cares and responsibilities,

43:10.880 --> 43:13.757
"I bequeath the remainder of my estate,

43:13.967 --> 43:16.593
"which includes
Monahan's Department Store,

43:16.803 --> 43:19.179
estimated worth, $10 million."

43:19.389 --> 43:21.181
Oh!

43:21.391 --> 43:24.184
"If, and only if, her husband Monty

43:24.394 --> 43:26.186
can reform himself in one year."

43:26.396 --> 43:29.147
What kind of reform you talking' about?

43:29.357 --> 43:32.734
There is a codicil attached
to the will, Mr. Capalooti.

43:32.944 --> 43:35.612
- That's Capuletti.
- Mr. Capuletti.

43:35.822 --> 43:39.741
Which lists the activities
which are to be proscribed:

43:39.951 --> 43:44.788
That is, the things
you must refrain from.

43:52.338 --> 43:54.715
- No smoking.
- No philandering.

43:54.924 --> 43:56.925
- No gambling.
- No drugs.

43:57.135 --> 43:58.135
No alcohol.

43:58.344 --> 44:00.804
No alcohol? Does that go for beer too?

44:01.014 --> 44:02.222
Certainly.

44:02.432 --> 44:06.268
And you must weigh not more
than 175 pounds.

44:06.477 --> 44:07.728
Uh, question?

44:07.937 --> 44:11.773
Assuming Monty can't reform,
perish the thought...

44:11.983 --> 44:14.776
Oh, then you get the money.

44:14.986 --> 44:16.820
I do?

44:29.083 --> 44:32.252
- Forget about it. I'm not doin' it.
- You're right, forget it.

44:32.462 --> 44:37.341
Daddy, come on, you can do it!
It's $10 million!

44:39.218 --> 44:40.761
Oh, and Mr. Capalooti,

44:40.970 --> 44:43.764
should you decide to accept these terms,

44:43.973 --> 44:47.351
remember we'll be watching you.

44:49.896 --> 44:53.857
I need a drink and a cigarette
so I can think this over, ya know.

44:55.777 --> 44:58.153
Twelve months? Forget about it.

44:58.363 --> 45:00.656
You can do that standing on your head.

45:00.865 --> 45:02.240
It's easy money.

45:02.533 --> 45:04.451
Hey, that's a lot of money, Monty.

45:04.661 --> 45:06.953
That could parlay
into a fortune for you.

45:08.164 --> 45:11.458
I couldn't care less,
Monty, but think of the kids.

45:12.001 --> 45:15.462
- Think about mommy.
- Think of your wife, and your kids.

45:19.050 --> 45:21.510
Think of me, ya bum!

46:09.642 --> 46:11.977
Monty, breakfast is ready.

46:13.229 --> 46:15.105
Oh, breakfast. Beautiful.

46:15.314 --> 46:17.649
I stopped smoking. I'm starvin'.

46:17.859 --> 46:20.235
- Dad, pass the syrup.
- Here, here.

46:22.238 --> 46:24.489
Rose, you gave me the wrong plate.

46:24.699 --> 46:26.992
Where's the rest of my eggs
and my home fries?

46:27.702 --> 46:30.662
These are the rest of your eggs,
these are your home fries,

46:30.872 --> 46:33.707
and this is applesauce.

46:38.463 --> 46:42.132
Belinda, I can't eat all my home fries.
Want some home fries?

46:42.341 --> 46:44.134
No, thanks.

46:44.343 --> 46:47.846
Here, Monty.
Oohhh, pass them to Belinda.

46:48.055 --> 46:50.307
If you wanna lose weight,
you should start now.

46:53.770 --> 46:55.645
Ooh, food.

46:55.855 --> 46:58.690
- It's a tough give-up.
- Allison, eat.

46:58.900 --> 47:01.735
Allison, you gotta eat.

47:02.278 --> 47:03.737
I know marriage is rough.

47:04.280 --> 47:07.199
It's not all moonlight and canoes.
That's in the movies.

47:07.408 --> 47:10.202
- I don't wanna talk about it.
- What's the matter with you?

47:10.411 --> 47:13.747
You don't eat. You don't talk to no one.

47:14.248 --> 47:16.666
You lock yourself in
your room all night.

47:16.876 --> 47:19.503
The way you're carrying on,
you'll never meet another guy.

47:27.136 --> 47:28.428
What'd I say?

47:28.638 --> 47:30.430
"You'll never meet another guy."

47:30.640 --> 47:32.349
Take out the garbage.

47:34.018 --> 47:36.186
Take out the garbage.

47:36.395 --> 47:39.648
I didn't even eat,
I gotta take out the garbage.

47:42.819 --> 47:44.778
Hi.

47:56.833 --> 47:59.292
She ain't worth $10 million.

48:03.422 --> 48:05.423
$5 million, maybe.

49:02.148 --> 49:04.566
Hey, not here! Not here!

49:04.775 --> 49:07.569
I'm your new neighbor, Bill Jones.
You can call me Bill.

49:07.778 --> 49:10.530
Not here! Why don't you take
him on your property, huh?

49:10.740 --> 49:12.949
Take it easy, you interrupt
King's business he gets very upset.

49:13.159 --> 49:15.577
What makes you think I wanna
inherit his business?

49:15.786 --> 49:17.579
If you feel so bad, I'll clean it up.

49:17.788 --> 49:18.538
Sure.

49:18.748 --> 49:22.167
So you're Monty Capuletti.
Congratulations on your daughter's wedding.

49:22.376 --> 49:25.962
Some party, I heard about.
What am I telling you for, you were there.

49:26.172 --> 49:29.549
Look, I'm your next door neighbor now,
so we gotta get to be good buddies.

49:29.759 --> 49:32.969
I wanna have a relationship. Most important
thing for us, we gotta have a good rapport.

49:33.179 --> 49:35.055
Wait till you meet Ginger.
She's my better half.

49:35.264 --> 49:38.558
I already saw your better half.
In fact, I saw more than half.

49:38.768 --> 49:41.561
She's a dynamite girl. I met her
in Vegas a couple of years ago.

49:41.771 --> 49:44.606
Oh, man, she's a loving,
caring, sharing person.

49:44.815 --> 49:46.483
Someone maybe one day you
can become friendly with.

49:46.692 --> 49:48.652
I needed you two to move in next door.

49:48.861 --> 49:51.363
I'm nervous enough this morning.
